      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start for the overview. To really win the debate, I need more specific \"logic\" to use in my rebuttals. Like, if my opponent brings up the racial inequality aspect, how can I pivot back to the idea that these policies actually served a functional purpose for urban stability? Specifically, can you expand on the argument regarding property value protection? I need to be able to argue that these measures prevented \"neighborhood decline\" and kept certain areas more stable and predictable for the residents within them. How would a formal debate case structure that argument?",
